🛠️ Phase 1: Environment & Phone Setup

Step 1: Install ADB on your Computer
If you haven't already, your system needs the standalone Android Debug Bridge platform tools.
1.Download the official SDK Platform-Tools for Windows/Mac directly from Google.
2.Extract the ZIP folder to a safe place (e.g., C:\platform-tools).
3.Add that path to your computer’s System Environment Variables under Path so your terminal recognizes the adb command from any directory.
4.Open a command prompt and type adb version to confirm it works.

Step 2: Prepare Your Phone
1.Go to your phone’s Settings > About Phone and tap Build Number 7 times until it says "You are now a developer!"
2.Back out and open the newly unlocked Developer Options menu.
3.Turn on USB Debugging.
4.(Crucial for automation) Turn on USB Debugging (Security settings) if your phone has it (common on Xiaomi/Oppo/Vivo). This setting explicitly grants ADB permission to simulate hardware input taps and type text strings remotely.

📐 Phase 2: Precise Screen Calibration

Because every phone screen features a slightly different aspect ratio (e.g., 16:9, 19.5:9, 20:9), your template-matching bounding boxes must line up perfectly with your phone's real UI elements.

Step 3: Turn on Coordinate Overlays
1.Inside your phone’s Developer Options, scroll down and enable Pointer Location.
2.This places a status bar at the very top of your glass display showing live $X$ and $Y$ coordinates whenever and wherever you press down.

Step 4: Map the Enemy Draft Slots
1.Boot up MLBB on your phone, navigate to Custom > Draft Pick, and fill the game slots with 9 Computer AI bots so you have infinite time to inspect the layout.
2.Press your finger to the Top-Left corner of the first enemy avatar slot at the top right of the screen. Look at the top status bar and write down the exact (X, Y) values.
3.Press your finger to the Bottom-Right corner of that same slot. Write down those (X, Y) values.
4.Convert those absolute numbers into decimals based on your phone's total width and height. For instance, if your phone is 2400 \times 1080, and your top-left corner box registers at X=2112, Y=162:
                      2112
        X_Start_Pct = ____ = 0.88
                      2400

                      162
        Y_Start_Pct = ---- = 0.15
                      1080
5.Open your updated adb_bot.py script and drop those calculated decimals into your self.enemy_slots_pct array! Do this for all 5 slots.

🚀 Phase 3: Running the Full Live System
Now that the physical elements are perfectly calibrated, you can run your data streams simultaneously.

Step 5: Start the Streamlit Visual Dashboard
Open a dedicated terminal window on your PC, navigate directly to your code directory, and boot up your local interface framework:

* streamlit run app.py

This launches your web browser tracker interface locally on http://localhost:8501. Keep this window open on half of your monitor.

